{"lemma":"أَغْنِياءُ","slug":"أَغْنِياءُ","root":"غ.ن.#","root_slug":"غ-ن-_","root_link":"/words/roots/غ-ن-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"غَنِيّ","root":"غني","pos":"N","occurrence_count":24},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["adj","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":9},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n32540","","n32542","n32543","n32549"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%BA%D9%92%D9%86%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%A1%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be free from want"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be content, to be satisfied"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be rich, to be wealthy"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to marry"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to inhabit, dwell, settle"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to remain, continue to be"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to live, exist"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"rich, wealthy","examples":[{"text":"لِلْفُقَرَاءِ ٱلَّذِينَ أُحْصِرُوا فِي سَبِيلِ ٱللّٰهِ لَا يَسْتَطِيعُونَ ضَرْبًا فِي ٱلْأَرْضِ يَحْسَبُهُمُ ٱلْجَاهِلُ أَغْنِيَاءَ مِنَ ٱلتَّعَفُّفِ تَعْرِفُهُم بِسِيمَاهُمْ لَا يَسْأَلُونَ ٱلنَّاسَ إِلْحَافًا وَمَا تُنْفِقُوا مِنْ خَيْرٍ فَإِنَّ ٱللّٰهَ بِهِ عَلِيمٌ","english":"[Charity is] for the poor who have been restricted for the cause of God, unable to move about in the land. An ignorant one would think them self-sufficient because of their restraint, but you will know them by their sign. They do not ask people persistently. And whatever you spend of good: indeed, God is Knowing of it."}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"free from need","examples":[{"text":"وَكَذَلِكَ ﴿لِنُحْيِيَ بِهِ بَلْدَةً مَيْتًا﴾ يُرِيدُ بَعْضَ بِلَادِ هَؤُلَاءِ الْمُتَبَاعِدِينَ عَنْ مَظَانِّ الْمَاءِ بِخِلَافِ سُكَّانِ الْمُدُنِ فَإِنَّهُمْ قَرِيبُونَ مِنَ الْأَوْدِيَةِ وَالْأَنْهَارِ وَالْعُيُونِ فَهُمْ غَنِيُّونَ غَالِبًا عَنْ سَقْيِ مَاءِ الْمَطَرِ[…]","english":"And as it is [said in the verse:] \"So that We might revive [by sending the rain] a lifeless land...\"; some nations would like those who are far from a habitat with water, as opposed to the inhabitants of jurisdictions because [the latter] are [already] near the stream-beds and the rivers and the springs, so they are in no need of [and have already] overcome [the dependency upon] irrigation of rainwater […]"}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ɣa.niː/","/ɣa.nijj/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n32540","headword_ar":"غَنِىَ","root":"gnY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, MA, Msb, K, *) from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaAl","text_ar":"المَال"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yagonaY","text_ar":"يَغْنَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ginFY","text_ar":"غِنًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * MA, Msb, K *) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ganaA='N","text_ar":"غَنَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (MA, K, * TK, [but the latter is app. held by some to be a simple subst.,])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, free from want; in the state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition, of having no wants;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and also,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of having"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2302},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"few wants;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a state of competence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sufficiency;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rich,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wealthy;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlginaY","text_ar":"الغِنَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"being"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the contr."},{"kind":"text","text":"of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfaqoru","text_ar":"الفَقْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlganaA='u","text_ar":"الغَنَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, TA;) and thus denoting the absence, or non-existence, of wants, which is [properly, or strictly speaking,] attributable to none but God; and also the paucity of wants; (TA;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlyasaAru","text_ar":"اليَسَارُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) and the epithet applied to him of whom this is said is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ganiY~N","text_ar":"غَنِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaAnK","text_ar":"غَانٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) [or both, for] both signify the same [as will be shown below]. (K.) One says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ganiYa","text_ar":"غَنِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AstgnY","text_ar":"استغنى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tgn~Y","text_ar":"تغنّى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tgAnY","text_ar":"تغانى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AgtnY","text_ar":"اغتنى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA, [but wanting in the CK, and app. in several copies of the K, though it is said in one place in the K, as it is in the S, that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tgn~Y","text_ar":"تغنّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AstgnY","text_ar":"استغنى"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) all having one and the same meaning, and followed by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bihi","text_ar":"بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as therewith signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, free from want; in the state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition, of having no want,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"need;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a state of competence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by means of it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, sufficed by it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and hence,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, content,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"satisfied, with it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosa min~aA mano lamo yatagan~a","text_ar":"لَيْسَ مِنَّا مَنْ لَمْ يَتَغَنَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAlquroA=ni","text_ar":"بِالقُرْا=نِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,) a saying of the Prophet, (Msb,) mentioned in a trad., (TA,) means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn lm","text_ar":"من لم"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yasotagoni","text_ar":"يَسْتَغْنِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is not of us who is not content,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"satisfied, with the Kur-án"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: so says Sufyán Ibn-'Oyeyneh; not regarding it as meaning the utterance of the voice [in chanting]: and A 'Obeyd says that this obtains extensively in the speech of the Arabs; that they say ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tagan~ayotu","text_ar":"تَغَنَّيْتُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tagaAnayotu","text_ar":"تَغَانَيْتُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aisotagonayotu","text_ar":"اِسْتَغْنَيْتُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Az, Msb, TA.) And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ganiYa Eanohu","text_ar":"غَنِىَ عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ginFY","text_ar":"غِنًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gunoyaAnN","text_ar":"غُنْيَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was in no need of it"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Enh","text_ar":"عنه"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AstgnY","text_ar":"استغنى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gnh","text_ar":"غنه"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^agonaY","text_ar":"اَغْنَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which seems to be rarely used in this sense]: and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gunoyapN","text_ar":"غُنْيَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state of being in no need:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaAnKi","text_ar":"غَانٍِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", a man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"free from need."},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA","text_ar":"مَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eanohu","text_ar":"عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yasotagoniY","text_ar":"يَسْتَغْنِى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is not without need,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not free from want, of it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"him."},{"kind":"text","text":"] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ganiYa bihi Eanohu","text_ar":"غَنِىَ بِهِ عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eano gayorihi","text_ar":"عَنْ غَيْرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gunoyapN","text_ar":"غُنْيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gunoyapN","text_ar":"غُنْيَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the subst., (Msb,) meaning ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AstgnY","text_ar":"استغنى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was sufficed by it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was satisfied,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"content, with it, so as to be in no need,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so as to be free from want, of it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of another thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and the epithet is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ganiY~N","text_ar":"غَنِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) And [in like manner]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ganiyati AlmaroA^apu bizawojihaA","text_ar":"غَنِيَتِ المَرْاَةُ بِزَوْجِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eano gayorihi","text_ar":"عَنْ غَيْرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gunoyaAnN","text_ar":"غُنْيَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ganaA='N","text_ar":"غَنَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also, (TA,) meaning ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aisotagonat","text_ar":"اِسْتَغْنَت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The woman was satisfied,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"content, with her husband, so as to have no want of other than him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, K) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ganiyato","text_ar":"غَنِيَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[alone], (K, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ginFA","text_ar":"غِنًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ginFY","text_ar":"غِنًى"},{"kind":"text","text":", or perhaps a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ganaA='N","text_ar":"غَنَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in the next preceding sentence],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a woman)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, such as is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaAniyapN","text_ar":"غَانِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaAnK","text_ar":"غَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ganiYa","text_ar":"غَنِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TK,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ginFY","text_ar":"غِنًى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TK,) also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He married,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"took a wife;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tgn~Y","text_ar":"تغنّى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (see Ham p. 226 l. 1, where"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tagan~ato","text_ar":"تَغَنَّتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"occurs said of a woman as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she married;"},{"kind":"text","text":")] syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tazaw~aja","text_ar":"تَزَوَّجَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K, * TK. [In the K, only the inf. n. of the former verb in this sense is mentioned;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlginaY","text_ar":"الغِنَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"being there expl. in some copies as signifying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~azaw~uju","text_ar":"التَّزَوُّجُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and in others,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~azowiyju","text_ar":"التَّزْوِيجُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) Hence the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlginaY HiSonN liloEazabi","text_ar":"الغِنَى حِصْنٌ لِلْعَزَبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Marriage is a bulwark to him who has no wife;"},{"kind":"text","text":"protecting him from the attacks of seductive women by rendering him free from the want of them]: mentioned by Az. (TA.) ―         -b3-  Also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ganiYa","text_ar":"غَنِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ginFY","text_ar":"غِنًى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He dwelt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAlmakaAni","text_ar":"بِالمَكَانِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the place:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ganiYa Alqawomu fiY daArihimo","text_ar":"غَنِىَ القَوْمُ فِى دَارِهِمْ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party, dwelt long in their place of abode:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ganiYa fiY makaAni ka*aA","text_ar":"غَنِىَ فِى مَكَانِ كَذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He dwelt long in such a place, satisfied,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"content, therewith, so as to be in no need of any other."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib, TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaA^ano lamo yagonawoA fiyhaA","text_ar":"كَاَنْ لَمْ يَغْنَوْا فِيهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [vii. 90 and xi. 71 and 98], means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"As though they had not dwelt therein."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [See also the last sentence but two in this paragraph.] ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He lived;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaA$a","text_ar":"عَاشَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqiYa","text_ar":"بَقِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ganiytu laka min~iY biAlmawad~api","text_ar":"غَنِيتُ لَكَ مِنِّى بِالمَوَدَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqiytu","text_ar":"بَقِيتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I remained,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"have remained, constant to thee with my love,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affection"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (ISd, K, TA: in the CK [erroneously]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ganayotu","text_ar":"غَنَيْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b6-  [And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna","text_ar":"كَانَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qado A^agonaY AlHabiyba","text_ar":"قَدْ اَغْنَى الحَبِيبَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuSaAfiYa","text_ar":"المُصَافِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in a verse of Ibn-Mukbil, means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akuwnu","text_ar":"اَكُونُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHabiyba","text_ar":"الحَبِيبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Certainly I will be,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shall be, the sincere friend"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ganiyato daArunaA tihaAmapa","text_ar":"غَنِيَتْ دَارُنَا تِهَامَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) in a verse of another poet, (TA,) means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAnato","text_ar":"كَانَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Our place of abode was Tihámeh"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K, TA.) And one says of a thing when it has perished, passed away, or come to nought,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaA^ano lamo yagona biAlA^amosi","text_ar":"كَاَنْ لَمْ يَغْنَ بِالاَمْسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaA^ano lamo","text_ar":"كَاَنْ لَمْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yakuno","text_ar":"يَكُنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"As though it had not been in existence yesterday"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Az, TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ganiYa","text_ar":"غَنِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laqiYa","text_ar":"لَقِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) [SM doubts this; saying,] thus in the copies; but perhaps it should be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqiYa","text_ar":"بَقِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", a signification of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ganiYa","text_ar":"غَنِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to ISd and the K [and mentioned above]: (TA:) [it appears, however, to be correct; for it is said that]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA ganiytu","text_ar":"مَا غَنِيتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnFA","text_ar":"فُلَانًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lamo A^aloqahu","text_ar":"لَمْ اَلْقَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I did not meet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"meet with,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"find,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have not met,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such a one"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (JK.) [Accord. to the TK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ganiYa","text_ar":"غَنِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"followed by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bihi","text_ar":"بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laqiY","text_ar":"لَقِى"},{"kind":"text","text":": but this is perhaps said conjecturally.]"}],"source_refs":["Msb","S","TA","K","TK","T"]},{"entry_id":"n32542","headword_ar":"غَنًى","root":"gnY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) with fet-h, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maqoSuwr","text_ar":"مَقْصُور"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"may^in~apN","text_ar":"مَيِنَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; so in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"makaAnu ka*aA ganFY mino","text_ar":"مَكَانُ كَذَا غَنًى مِنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnK","text_ar":"فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a place is meet, fit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proper, for such a one;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though meaning a place of freedom from want]; as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"minohu","text_ar":"مِنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"magonFY","text_ar":"مَغْنًى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n32543","headword_ar":"غِنًى","root":"gnY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ganaA='N","text_ar":"غَنَا=ءٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify the same; (MA, K;) both are inf. ns. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ganiYa","text_ar":"غَنِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (MA:) [see the first sentence of this art.: used as simple substs., they mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Freedom from need"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"want; competence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sufficiency;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"richness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wealthiness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ginFY","text_ar":"غِنًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ganiYa","text_ar":"غَنِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ganaA='N","text_ar":"غَنَا=ءٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"competence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sufficiency;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb;) as in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosa Einodahu ganaA='N","text_ar":"لَيْسَ عِنْدَهُ غَنَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He has not competence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sufficiency:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ganaA='N","text_ar":"غَنَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"profit, utility,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"avail;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;) and you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA ganaA='a Einodahu","text_ar":"لَا غَنَا=ءَ عِنْدَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man who is not profitable to any one:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dadaAnN","text_ar":"دَدَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; [and in like manner this phrase, occurring in the S voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dadaAnN","text_ar":"دَدَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is expl. in the PS:]) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gunowapN","text_ar":"غُنْوَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ginFY","text_ar":"غِنًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liY Eanohu gunowapN","text_ar":"لِى عَنْهُ غُنْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have no need of it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K and TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gnw","text_ar":"غنو"},{"kind":"text","text":":) so says Ks: but, as ISd says, the word commonly known is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gunoyapN","text_ar":"غُنْيَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA in that art.;) which see in two places in the former half of the first paragraph of this art.: this last word [said in the S to be an inf. n.] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ginoyapN","text_ar":"غِنْيَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gunowapN","text_ar":"غُنْوَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gunoyaAnN","text_ar":"غُنْيَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is said in the S and in one place in the K to be an inf. n.] are substs. having one and the same meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn."},{"kind":"text","text":"with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ginFY","text_ar":"غِنًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"used as a simple subst.]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA lah Eanohu ginFY","text_ar":"مَا لَه عَنْهُ غِنًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the CK erroneously"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ganFY","text_ar":"غَنًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gunoyapN","text_ar":"غُنْيَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gunoyaAnN","text_ar":"غُنْيَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"magonFY","text_ar":"مَغْنًى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"mean [lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He has not freedom from need of it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and hence,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he has not any means,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"way, of separating himself from,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"avoiding, it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bud~N","text_ar":"بُدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) and one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eani","text_ar":"عَنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Aln~ikaAHi gunoyapN","text_ar":"فِى النِّكَاحِ غُنْيَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~ifaAHi","text_ar":"السِّفَاحِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In marriage is freedom from need of fornication"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A and Msb in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sfH","text_ar":"سفح"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA","text_ar":"مَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna Eano Zahori ginFY","text_ar":"كَانَ عَنْ ظَهْرِ غِنًى"},{"kind":"text","text":", in a trad. respecting alms, means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What is over and above that which suffices for the sustenance of the household,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"family."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["MA","Msb","K"]},{"entry_id":"n32549","headword_ar":"غَنِىٌّ","root":"gnY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaAnK","text_ar":"غَانٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 1, former half; each in two places: both signify ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Free from want;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a state of competence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sufficiency;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rich,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wealthy;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"possessing much property"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wealth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA:) pl. of the former"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^agoniyaA='u","text_ar":"اَغْنِيَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb, TA.) See an ex. of the former in a verse cited above, conj. 6. One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaA ganiY~N bika*aA Eano","text_ar":"اَنَا غَنِىٌّ بِكَذَا عَنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gayorihi","text_ar":"غَيْرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I am sufficed by such a thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"satisfied,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"content, with it, so as to be free from want of another thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlganiY~u","text_ar":"الغَنِىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as a name of God signifies ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Self-sufficient;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He who has no need of any one in any thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]}}